Apple has announced it will be donating undisclosed amounts to relief efforts in Asia following separate disasters, including multiple building fires in Hong Kong and a series of severe storms and flooding across Thailand, Indonesia, Malaysia, and Sri Lanka.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2023/09/Apple-Logo-Spotlight.jpg" alt="" width="1600" height="900" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-912758" /><br/>
"Heartbroken by the devastating fire in Hong Kong," said Apple CEO Tim Cook, in a <a href="https://x.com/tim_cook/status/1994319685089702129">social media post</a> last week. "Everyone affected is in our thoughts and we are thankful for the first responders. Apple is donating to relief efforts on the ground."<br/>
<br/>
"Storms across Thailand, Indonesia, Malaysia, and Sri Lanka have devastated communities," said Cook, in <a href="https://x.com/tim_cook/status/1995900164519985451">another post</a> today. "At Apple, we're thinking of everyone affected, and will be donating to relief and building efforts on the ground."<br/>
<br/>
Apple has donated to the Red Cross for relief efforts in the past.<br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/12/02/apple-donating-to-relief-efforts-in-asia/">Apple Donating to Relief Efforts in Asia After Deadly Fire and Storms</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/apple-donating-to-relief-efforts-in-asia-after-deadly-fire-and-storms.2473968/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>